VioMATRIXC Build And Install Notes
==================================

This repository is a fork of ngspice customized for VioSpice. The build system
is still the standard autotools/ngspice layout, but the preferred fork
configuration uses `--enable-vicompat`.


Requirements
------------

Minimum tools:

* `gcc` or another C compiler
* `make`
* `autoconf`
* `automake`
* `libtool`
* `bison`
* `flex`

For the console/X11 build you will also need the usual X11 and readline
development packages used by ngspice.


Recommended Linux Console Build
-------------------------------

    ./autogen.sh
    mkdir -p release
    cd release
    ../configure --with-x --enable-cider --enable-vicompat
    make -j"$(nproc)"

This produces a console build with the VioSpice compatibility mode enabled by
default.


Recommended Linux Shared-Library Build
--------------------------------------

    ./autogen.sh
    mkdir -p releasesh
    cd releasesh
    ../configure --with-ngshared --enable-cider --enable-vicompat
    make -j"$(nproc)"

Use this variant when embedding the simulator in VioSpice or another host
application.


Helper Scripts
--------------

The repository includes wrapper scripts for the two common fork workflows:

* `compile_linux_vicompat.sh`
* `compile_linux_shared_vicompat.sh`

These scripts:

* run `./autogen.sh`
* create the build directory if needed
* configure with `--enable-vicompat`
* run `make clean`, `make`, and `make install`
* save build logs in the build directory

Review the install prefix inside the scripts before using them on a system
where `/usr` or `/usr/local` is not appropriate.


Fork-Specific Configure Flag
----------------------------

`--enable-vicompat` changes the default startup compatibility mode by setting:

    set vicompat=lt

in the generated `spinit` file.

This is the main fork-specific build option and should be considered the
default for VioSpice-oriented builds.


